archives.gov.uk/domesday/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Domesday","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705184,"age":41,"year":"1096","julianDay":2121366,"title":"The Crusades","description":"A series of religious wars between Christians and Muslims, known as the Crusades, occurred between 1096 and 1291, and played a large role in European Christian dominance in the Middle East.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/middle-ages/crusades","urlTitle":"History - The Crusades","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705185,"age":51,"year":"1106","julianDay":2125018,"title":"The Battle of Tichebray","description":"King Henry I defeated and captured his brother, Robert of Normandy, at the Battle of Tinchebray in 1106. Robert remained in captivity until his death in 1134.","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"When Siward de Arden was born about 1055, in Warwickshire, England, his father, Thurkil de Arden, was 17 and his mother, Leverunia d'Ardene of Mercia, was 7. He married Cecilia before 1078, in England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 2 sons and 1 daughter. He died about 1139, in England, United Kingdom, at the age of 86."},"et":{"about 1055–Abt 1139":"umbes 1055–umbes 1139","1055–1139":"1055–1139","1080–Female":"1080–Surnud","1082–Male":"1082–Surnud","1098–1166":"1098–1166","–Female":"Surnud","1040–1095":"1040–1095","1050–1097":"1050–1097","1080":"1080","before 1078":"enne 1078","Abt 1139":"umbes 1139","1066":"1066","1055":"1055","1098":"1098","1097":"1097","1086":"1086","1096":"1096","1095":"1095","1040":"1040","1050":"1050","1082":"1082","Abt 1098":"umbes 1098","1106":"1106","1139":"1139","Abt 1095":"umbes 1095","1166":"1166","ABT 1082":"umbes 1082","about 1055":"umbes 1055","of Ratley, Warwick, Eng":"Ratley, Warwickshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Warwickshire, England":"Warwickshire, England","England, United Kingdom":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1055–Abt 1139":"noin 1055–noin 1139","1055–1139":"1055–1139"